A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 3 of Title 35 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to Georgia Crime Information Center, so as to provide that the Department of
3 Human Services shall be authorized to access restricted and sealed information to determine
4 eligibility for employment, verify eligibility for foster parents, or conduct regulatory
5 oversight in certain instances; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and
6 for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Article 2 of Chapter 3 of Title 35 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
10 Georgia Crime Information Center, is amended by revising paragraph (6) of subsection (a),
11 by revising subparagraphs (v)(1)(E) and (v)(1)(F), and by adding a new subparagraph to
12 paragraph (1) of subsection (v) of Code Section 35-3-37, relating to criminal history record
13 information, review, corrections, and restriction of access for certain dispositions, to read as
14 follows:
15 "(6) 'Restrict,' 'restricted,' or 'restriction' means that the criminal history record
16 information of an individual relating to a particular offense shall be available only to
